        "highlights": [
            {
                "id": 529616672,
                "text": "It all starts with the universally applicable premise that people want to be understood and accepted. Listening is the cheapest, yet most effective concession we can make to get there. By listening intensely, a negotiator demonstrates empathy and shows a sincere desire to better understand what the other side is experiencing.",
                "location": 0,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616672"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616673,
                "text": "Research shows that the best way to deal with negativity is to observe it, without reaction and without judgment. Then consciously label each negative feeling and replace it with positive, compassionate, and solution-based thoughts.",
                "location": 1,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616673"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616674,
                "text": "When people are in a positive frame of mind, they think more quickly, and are more likely to collaborate and problem-solve (instead of fight and resist). It applies to the smile-er as much as to the smile-ee: a smile on your face, and in your voice, will increase your own mental agility.",
                "location": 2,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616674"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616675,
                "text": "Great negotiators are able to question the assumptions that the rest of the involved players accept on faith or in arrogance, and thus remain more emotionally open to all possibilities, and more intellectually agile to a fluid situation.",
                "location": 3,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.157Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616675"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616676,
                "text": "The goal is to identify what your counterparts actually need (monetarily, emotionally, or otherwise) and get them feeling safe enough to talk and talk and talk some more about what they want.",
                "location": 4,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616676"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616677,
                "text": "Effective negotiation is applied people smarts, a psychological edge in every domain of life: how to size someone up, how to influence their sizing up of you, and how to use that knowledge to get what you want.",
                "location": 5,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616677"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616678,
                "text": "But neither wants nor needs are where we start; it begins with listening, making it about the other people, validating their emotions, and creating enough trust and safety for a real conversation to begin.",
                "location": 6,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616678"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616679,
                "text": "To get real leverage, you have to persuade them that they have something concrete to lose if the deal falls through.",
                "location": 7,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616679"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616680,
                "text": "The first step of doing so is listing every terrible thing your counterpart could say about you, in what I call an accusation audit.",
                "location": 8,
                "location_type": "order",
                "note": "",
                "color": "",
                "highlighted_at": null,
                "created_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "updated_at": "2023-05-15T01:05:02.158Z",
                "external_id": null,
                "end_location": null,
                "url": null,
                "book_id": 27728455,
                "tags": [],
                "is_favorite": false,
                "is_discard": false,
                "readwise_url": "https://readwise.io/open/529616680"
            },
            {
                "id": 529616681,
                "text": "Going too fast is one of the mistakes all negotiators are prone to making.",
                "location": 9,
